==English==

===Transitive verb===
'''to underpin'''

#To [[support]] from [[below]] with [[prop]]s or [[masonry]].
#* The mine roof was '''underpinned''' to prevent further collapse.
#To give support to.
#* Public confidence in politicians must '''underpin''' our democracy.

